    <body>
      <head>Lisl (Liesl) Schiff</head>
      <div>

        <p>Daughter of <ref cRef="entity-000782">Paul</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-000781">Anna
            Schiff</ref>. Nothing is known of her life other than her <ref cRef="entity-000781"
            >mother</ref>’s description in 1926: “I would like to protest against <ref
            cRef="entity-000782">Paul</ref>’s assertion that our child is in no way different from
          other children. Above all Lisl is much more mischievous and wilder than other children,
          and the reverse side of this coin is the most extreme sensibility, thus directly the
          opposite of the first-named characteristics.” (<ref type="correspondence"
            cRef="OJ-14-8_10">OJ 14/8, [10]</ref>, February 1, 1926)</p>
      </div>
    </body>

